> The Decommodification principle is a troubling one for Larry as it is so =
often interrupted to mean 'thy shall never make a profit', and it was never=
 meant to imply that. Larry has always recognized the need for individuals =
and entities to be able to sustain themselves. The practice of gifting at t=
he events is intended to remind us of to be mindful of our transactions, to=
 value the interpersonal nature that they can-should consist of. This build=
s community. You will see the BM Project affiliate itself with events or un=
dertakings where those involved sell things, and not just ice or coffee. Bu=
t it's commerce that seeks to build or sustain community not one
